The paper focuses on requirements engineering and quality aspects in software ecosystems, which are complex systems involving multiple stakeholders and software components. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper discusses open innovation processes, which are related to social and information systems (cs.SI). The paper also analyzes modeling approaches, which could fall under cs.CY (Computational Geometry) or cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper discusses quality attributes such as security, performance, reliability, safety, maintainability, transparency, and usability, which could fall under various sub-categories, but cs.SE and cs.SI are the most relevant.
